{"word":"ἱστίον","slug":"ἱστίον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἱστίον, τό</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἱστός\">ἱστός</a></el> ‘<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a> standing upright’ as a ‘mast’ on a ship, or the vertical ‘beam’ of an ancient loom; <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἱστίον\">ἱστίον</a></el> is a logical expression for a sail connected to a mast or produced at a loom] <b>a sail <a href='B:510 27:15'>Ac 27:15</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>, 17 <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἵστημι/ἱστάνω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἱστορέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}